quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  3,92,"You cannot attain to righteousness until you spend freely of what you love. But what you spend, of that Allah is aware"
  3,93,"All food was lawful to the children of Israel save what Israel made unlawful to itself before the Torah was revealed. Say, \"Bring the Torah and recite it, if you speak the truth"
  3,94,"But whoever invents against Allah a lie, after that, they are, indeed, the wrong-doers"
  3,95,"Say, \"Allah speaks the truth, then follow the faith of Abraham, a \"Hanif\" (an upright or righteous man), who was not of the idolaters"
  3,96,"Verily, the first House founded for men was surely that at Bekkah (Mecca), a blessed place and a guidance to the worlds"
  3,97,"Therein are manifest signs - Abraham´s station, and whoever enters it is safe. It is a duty to Allah for man to make the pilgrimage unto the House, for whoever can find his way there (or can afford it). But whoever disbelieves - Allah is Independent"
  3,98,"Say, \"O people of the Book! Why do you disbelieve in Allah´s revelations, when Allah is witness of what you do"
  3,99,"Say, \"O people of the Book! Why do you turn from the way of Allah him who believes, craving to make it crooked, when you are yourselves witnesses (of Allah´s covenant)? But Allah is not unmindful of what you do"
  3,100,"O you who believe! If you obey the sect of those to whom the Book was brought, they will turn you from believers to unbelievers again"